<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a7960b2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s7462"><num value="7462">§ 7462.</num><heading> International cybersecurity technical standards</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a7960b3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s7462/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director, in coordination with appropriate Federal authorities, shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a7960b4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s7462/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> as appropriate, ensure coordination of Federal agencies engaged in the development of international technical standards related to information system security; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a7960b5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s7462/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> not later than 1 year after <date date="2014-12-18">December 18, 2014</date>, develop and transmit to Congress a plan for ensuring such Federal agency coordination.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7a7960b6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s7462/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Consultation with the private sector</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In carrying out the activities specified in subsection (a)(1), the Director shall ensure consultation with appropriate private sector stakeholders.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7a7960b7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/274/tV/s502">Pub. L. 113–274, title V, § 502</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2986">128 Stat. 2986</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
